Module nl.naturalis.common
Package nl.naturalis.common.time

Class FuzzyDate

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.naturalis.common.time.FuzzyDate
  • public final class FuzzyDate
extends Object
    A FuzzyDate represents a date of which at least the year is known. You can retrieve regular java.time objects from it and it stores the verbatim date string from which it was created as well as the ParseInfo instance used to parse the verbatim date string. You obtain an instance by calling FuzzyDateParser.parse.

      • isFuzzyTime

        public boolean isFuzzyTime()
        Returns true if either the hour or the minute is unknown, false if both are known. Seconds are ignored, so time is not regarded as fuzzy if hour and minute are known but the second is not. If seconds are important, use the isSupported method on the TemporalAccessor instance returned by getTemporalAccessor.
